Quotation of the Day: Teachers Walk Out in 2 States as Fervor Spreads
“We’re going to have a lot of teachers at the ballot box who I don’t think would normally go in a midterm year. If I were a legislator right now, I’d be honestly sweating bullets.”
NOAH KARVELIS, an elementary school music teacher in Arizona and a leader among teachers there seeking better pay.
